```

## Summary

| Concern                     | Component                                                        |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Schema and actions          | Ash resource DSL                                                 |
| Column layout + compression | Parquet via Explorer / Polars                                    |
| File storage                | S3 via ExAws                                                     |
| Transaction log             | Postgres (`delta_tables`, `delta_commits`, `delta_files`)        |
| Row-group scan              | DuckDB via Duckdbex                                              |
| Partition pruning           | `AshDelta.Pruner` → JSONB `@>` containment predicates          |
| Stats pruning               | `AshDelta.Pruner` → `column_stats` interval overlap predicates |
| SQL filter compilation      | `AshDelta.Sql` → parameterised DuckDB `WHERE` clause           |
| Compaction                  | `AshDelta.optimize/2`                                            |
| Retention                   | `AshDelta.vacuum/2`                                              |
| Time travel                 | `Ash.Query.set_context(%{delta: %{version: v}})`                 |
| Derived tables              | `AshDelta.ViewLayer` + `AshDelta.refresh/2`                      |

AshDelta gives you a Lakehouse storage layer for append-heavy analytical workloads while keeping the full Ash resource model. Validations, policies, code interfaces, and other extensions all work exactly as they do on any other resource.
